<subSubSection id="46826547DC4140076B3EF8FCFA2A5799" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0E2736CCDC4140076B3EF8FCFA2A5799" blockId="28.[815,1474,1793,2041]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
DIAGNOSIS. Total length 
<quantity id="C9609B29DC4140076C2AF8FCFB3C5778" box="[1083,1203,1793,1817]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="45.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="37.0">37–54 mm</quantity>
. Base color yellow dark pattern reduced; telson brown; chelicerae pale yellow without reticulation. Pedipalp movable fingers bear 10–11 rows of granules, with 12 outer and inner denticles and fixed finger with 10–11 outer and inner denticles. Chela of pedipalp narrower in male, its length to width ratio 3.4–3.6 in females and 4.1–4.3 in males. Telson bulbous, with aculeus shorter than vesicle. Pectinal teeth number 
<quantity id="C9609B29DC4140076C09F81CFBFB5799" box="[1048,1140,2017,2041]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.858" metricValueMax="7.366" metricValueMin="6.35" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="27.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="25.0">25–29 in</quantity>
females and 
<quantity id="C9609B29DC4140076CEFF81CFAD55799" box="[1278,1370,2017,2041]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.001" metricValueMax="8.89" metricValueMin="7.112" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="31.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="28.0">28–35 in</quantity>
males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="46826547DC7D403B6860FDE7FE9C55F2" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0E2736CCDC7D403B6860FDE7FEA253F2" blockId="32.[113,771,538,914]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS. 
<bibRefCitation id="6A094B3DDC7D403B68E7FDE6FD975252" author="LEVY, G. &amp; P. AMITAI" bookContentInfo="132 pp." box="[246,536,538,563]" journalOrPublisher="Jerusalem: The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" refId="ref10220" refString="LEVY, G. &amp; P. AMITAI. 1980. Fauna Palaestina, Arachnida I. - Scorpiones. Jerusalem: The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, 132 pp." title="Fauna Palaestina, Arachnida I. - Scorpiones." type="book" year="1980">Levy &amp; Amitai (1980: 21)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6AA8FDE7FE7D5232" authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="zeylensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6AA8FDE7FEC85232" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A094B3DDC7D403B6946FDC7FE7D5232" author="Pocock" box="[343,498,570,594]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6A53FDC7FE1A5212" authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="berberensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6A53FDC7FF635212" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus berberensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A094B3DDC7D403B68EBFDA7FE1A5212" author="Pocock" box="[250,405,602,626]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. They argued that “examination of Pocock´s 
<typeStatus id="D123886EDC7D403B68EEFD86FEB852F3" box="[255,311,635,659]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">types</typeStatus>
and of additional material from 
<collectingCountry id="768F765CDC7D403B6ABDFD87FC8C52F2" box="[684,771,634,658]" name="Somalia" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Somalia</collectingCountry>
showed that these two forms are in fact the two sexes of the same subspecies, the first the male, the second the female.” We studied in detail a large collection of Somaliland specimens collected during expeditions of 2011–2019; this study, including cytogenetic and DNA analysis, confirmed that these two taxa are valid species. Here, we restore 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6AA8FCC7FE5B5312" authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="zeylensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6AA8FCC7FEB25312" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A094B3DDC7D403B6952FCA7FE5B5312" author="Pocock" box="[323,468,858,882]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from synonymy and elevate it to species rank.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E2736CCDC7D403B6860FC47FE9C55F2" blockId="32.[113,771,954,1426]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS ON LOCALITIES AND LIFE STRATEGY. In 2019, two of us (FK, HE) visited the city of Zeyla, the 
<typeStatus id="D123886EDC7D403B6A4DFC26FD045393" box="[604,651,987,1011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6860FC07FE495472" authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" box="[113,454,1018,1042]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6860FC07FEA95472" box="[113,294,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A094B3DDC7D403B693CFC07FE495472" author="Pocock" box="[301,454,1018,1042]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is an extremely hot place, with heavily salted soils. We collected scorpions several km from the city (
<geoCoordinate id="6BAC500BDC7D403B6902FBC7FE285432" box="[275,423,1082,1106]" degrees="11" direction="north" minutes="19" orientation="latitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" precision="1" seconds="31.2" value="11.325334">11°19'31.2&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="6BAC500BDC7D403B69A0FBC7FDCC5432" box="[433,579,1082,1106]" degrees="43" direction="east" minutes="22" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" precision="1" seconds="16.9" value="43.37136">43°22'16.9&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
) and found there 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6860FBA6FD9B5412" authority="(Pocock, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[113,532,1114,1138]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polystictus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6860FBA6FEE75412" box="[113,360,1114,1138]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Hottentotta polystictus</emphasis>
(Pocock, 1896)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6A0CFBA7FE8254F2" authority="(Pavesi, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Pavesi" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microbuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6A0CFBA7FC8C5412" box="[541,771,1114,1138]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Microbuthus litoralis</emphasis>
(Pavesi, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
(first record for Somaliland), 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6A5AFB87FEE454D2" authority="KovarIk et Lowe, 2016" authorityName="KovarIk et Lowe" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afar">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6A5AFB87FC8C54F2" box="[587,771,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Orthochirus afar</emphasis>
KovařÍk et Lowe, 2016
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B698EFB67FF2854B2" authority="Pocock, 1895" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Parabuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granimanus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B698EFB67FD2954D2" box="[415,678,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Parabuthus granimanus</emphasis>
Pocock, 1895
</taxonomicName>
(topotypes) but no 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B696FFB47FE4654B2" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[382,457,1210,1234]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B696FFB47FE4654B2" box="[382,457,1210,1234]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens. 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6A41FB47FC8C54B2" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" box="[592,771,1210,1234]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6A41FB47FC8C54B2" box="[592,771,1210,1234]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus zeylensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common in Gerissa, a very hot, sandy semidesert area (
<figureCitation id="96A32A49DC7D403B6868FB07FF565572" box="[121,217,1274,1298]" captionStart="Figures 100–101" captionStartId="17.[113,190,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[113,1474,234,1995]" captionTargetId="figure-35@17.[113,1474,234,1998]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 100–101: Localities. Figure 100. Buthus pococki sp. n., type locality (19SC). Figure 101. B. zeylensis, locality 19SH." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648410/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
) where we recorded also 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6A11FB06FD155572" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[512,666,1274,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polystictus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6A11FB06FD155572" box="[512,666,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">H. polystictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6ABAFB06FD735572" authorityName="KovarIk et Lowe" authorityYear="2016" box="[683,764,1274,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afar">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6ABAFB06FD735572" box="[683,764,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">O. afar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B68B4FAE6FEC75552" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" box="[165,328,1307,1330]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Parabuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granimanus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B68B4FAE6FEC75552" box="[165,328,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. granimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but also 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B69D5FAE7FE9B5532" authority="KovarIk, 2012" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Compsobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somalilandus">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B69D5FAE7FC8C5552" box="[452,771,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Compsobuthus somalilandus</emphasis>
KovařÍk, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6933FAC6FD4E5532" authority="KovarIk et al., 2018" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2018" box="[290,705,1338,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Gint" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gubanensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6933FAC6FE595532" box="[290,470,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Gint gubanensis</emphasis>
KovařÍk et al., 2018
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="D123886EDC7D403B6AC2FAC7FC8C5532" box="[723,771,1338,1362]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality), and 
<taxonomicName id="C9984D4FDC7D403B6902FAA7FC8C5512" authority="KovarIk et al., 2018" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2018" box="[275,771,1370,1397]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Neobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gubanensis">
<emphasis id="3CECEADEDC7D403B6902FAA7FD825512" box="[275,525,1370,1394]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Neobuthus gubanensis</emphasis>
KovařÍk et al., 2018
